dc_description_s: The GIS Department page on the Holmes County, Ohio website provides an access link to their FTP repository of geospatial datasets. Land survey, parcel, building footprint, and floodplain datasets are downloadable as zipped shapefiles. Aerial Imagery datasets dating from several years between 1974 and 2018 are available. Topographic elevation contours (2-foot) derived from a 2004 survey are also tiled and available to download as zipped shapefiles. A substantial collection of historic transportation atlases, tax maps, and land survey maps dating back to 1861 are available as PDF document downloads.
